The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Villa keep Spurs down
                                                                                                                                                                                           Villa keep Spurs down
                      
	London: Aston Villa kept Tottenham Hotspur bottom of the Premier League on Monday with a deserved 2-1 victory at White Hart Lane.         
	Villa scored after five minutes through Nigel Reo-Coker and again when Ashley Youngs shot squirmed under Tottenhams goalkeeper Heurelho Gomes.         
	Darren Bent deflected in a consolation late on for Tottenham who gave a debut to Roman Pavlyuchenko.                 (REUTERS)                                                                                                                      
